{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Pre-Merge Conversation Gate",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Before merging a PR, deterministically verify the orchestrator-led conversation is properly closed: the master-agent has the last word with a valid APPROVED-BY-MASTER-AGENT token, no tagged sub-agent was left without a reply, and CI is green. Blocks the merge if the conversation shape is invalid.",
  "when": {
    "type": "preToolUse",
    "toolTypes": [".*merge_pull_request.*", ".*kiroPowers.*"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "This hook fires before a merge OR before any GitHub Power call. FIRST determine whether the pending tool call is actually a pull-request merge (a direct `merge_pull_request` call, or a `kiroPowers` call whose `toolName` is `merge_pull_request`). If it is NOT a merge, allow it immediately and do nothing else. If it IS a merge, verify the conversation gate DETERMINISTICALLY:\n\n1. Fetch the full PR comment thread (chronological) via the GitHub Power.\n2. Load `.kiro/skills/pr-monitoring/turn-router-skill.js` and call `evaluateConversationGate({ comments, ciGreen, blockingIssues })` where `comments` is the ordered list of `{ body, authorLogin }`, `ciGreen` reflects the required GitHub checks, and `blockingIssues` is the count of unresolved ❌ items.\n3. If `mergeable` is false: DO NOT merge. Report each reason and take the corrective turn instead — typically the master must (a) ensure every tagged sub-agent has replied, then (b) post the closing comment carrying APPROVED-BY-MASTER-AGENT so the master has the last word. Only after a corrective turn may the merge be retried.\n4. If `mergeable` is true: allow the merge to proceed.\n\nThis gate enforces that the master-agent always posts the terminal message and that no sub-agent discussion was left hanging."
  }
}
